Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @slow cooked British pork{425%grams} from the packaging. 
Place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices. Season with @salt{} and 
@pepper{}, then cover loosely with #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf for ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams} with a #grater{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%milliliters}, @sugar for the 
dressing{1%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and 
@pepper{}. Set your salad dressing aside.

Quarter, core and thinly slice the @apple{1}(quartered, cored and thinly sliced) 
(no need to peel).

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} top down through the middle (but not all the 
way through).

Just before everything's ready, pop the buns onto a #baking tray{} and into the 
oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the pork is cooked, remove from the oven, reserve 1 tbsp of cooking juices 
per person, then discard the foil and any remaining cooking juices.

Use two #forks{} to shred the pork as finely as you can.

Once shredded, stir the @honey{30%grams} and @wholegrain mustard{17%grams} 
(add less if you'd prefer) into the pork. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Toss the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} and apple through the salad dressing.

Spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} onto the cut sides of the hot dog buns, then 
share them between your plates.

Load the honey-mustard pork into the buns, top with the cheese, then sprinkle 
over the @crispy onions{1%sachet}. Finish by drizzling the @BBQ sauce{48%grams} 
over the top.

Serve the wedges and apple salad alongside.

Enjoy!